Class:CLYH_0000002.text: phase of sexual reproduction in which certain cells of a female or male individual (parent) are transformed into specialized reproductive cells (gametes) that will initiate development of a progeny individual (offspring) upon fertilization.

Class:CLYH_0000015.text: matture female germ cell. not yet fertilized. Meiotic divisions complete. Spawned egg with female pronucleus.

Class:CLYH_0000018.text: Zygote fertilized egg, zygote nucleus forms at animal pole (about 0-50 min post fertilization at 18 degree celsius).

Class:CLYH_0000019.text: Two cell-stage embryo. First cleaveages unipolar and start at the animal pole (about 50-80 min post fertilization at 18 degree celsius).

Class:CLYH_0000020.text: Four cell-stage embryo. Second cleaveages unipolar and start at the animal pole (about 80-110 min post fertilization at 18 degree celsius).

Class:CLYH_0000022.text: Sixteen cell-stage embryo (about 2.5h post fertilization at 18 degree celsius).

Class:CLYH_0000024.text: sixty four cell-stage embryo (about 3h post fertilization at 18 degree celsius).

Class:CLYH_0000027.text: Cell contacts extended, cells polarised, nuclei apical (8h post fertilization at 18 degree celsius).

Class:CLYH_0000028.text: Cell polarized and columnar, nuclei apical (9- 10h post fertilization at 18 degree celsius).

Class:CLYH_0000030.text: Visible pointed oral pole but no cell ingression, ciliogenesis starting (12-13h post fertilization at 18 degree celsius).

Class:CLYH_0000031.text: A few cells ingressed at pointed oral pole, swimming started  (14-16h post fertilization at 18 degree celsius).

Class:CLYH_0000032.text: Ingression to fill balastotocoel half completed (17- 18h post fertilization at 18 degree celsius)

Class:CLYH_0000037.text: Competent to metamorphose as (72h post fertilization at 18 degree celsius)

Class:CLYH_0000038.text: Aged planula (> 3 days post fertilization at 18 degree celsius) but not received metamporphosis signal.
